# Frontend environment variables
#
# In production (Docker / nginx), no configuration is needed here.
# The nginx reverse proxy handles all /api/* routing to the backend,
# so the frontend always uses a relative /api base URL.
#
# For local development with `npm run dev`, the Vite dev server proxy
# in vite.config.ts forwards /api/* to http://localhost:8000.
# No .env file is required for local dev either.
#
# Only set these if you are running the frontend outside of the standard
# Docker Compose / Vite dev setup (e.g., a custom CDN deployment):
#
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend.example.com/api
